			<div class="comment-content comment-text">
				
				<p>It&#8217;s interesting how Ms. Host brought up the idea of strong female leads and how they can have many different personalities, but what makes them a strong lead is that they are willing to help and stand up when push comes to shoves. Usually I associate &#8220;strong female leads&#8221; with sarcastic, brash, gung-ho, fierce kinds of ladies, but there are female leads who are quiet, shy, and fearful, but they will come up and kick butt when they need to. (Actually, I just finished &#8220;The Two Princesses of Bamarre&#8221; and that got me thinking.)</p>
<p>Wonderful interview, you two! :D Lovely to see a little mention of Sophie in there too. ;)</p>
